fr.upmc.requestdispatcher.interfaces

Interface RequestDispatcherDynamicStateI

  • All Superinterfaces:
    fr.upmc.components.interfaces.DataOfferedI.DataI, fr.upmc.components.interfaces.DataRequiredI.DataI, java.io.Serializable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    RequestDispatcherDynamicState

    public interface RequestDispatcherDynamicStateI
extends fr.upmc.components.interfaces.DataOfferedI.DataI, fr.upmc.components.interfaces.DataRequiredI.DataI
    The interface RequestDispatcherDynamicStateI implements objects representing the dynamic state information of RDs transmitted through the RequestDispatcherDynamicStateDataI interface of RequestDispatcher components.

    Description

    The interface is used to type objects pulled from or pushed by a RD using a data interface in pull or push mode. It gives access to dynamic information, that is information subject to changes during the existence of the RD.

    Invariant

     invariant      true
